IN-041-05: EditorActionRegistry. Implement as a Rust struct in editor_action_registry.rs. It holds a BTreeMap<String, EditorActionNode> keyed by author_id. Provide:
  fn register(pane_type: PaneType, instance_index: usize) -> RegistrationHandle
  fn update_state(author_id: &str, state: EditorActionState)
  fn notify_accesskit_surface(surface: &AccessibilitySurface)
The registry should be Arc<Mutex<EditorActionRegistry>> so both the pane thread and the AccessKit polling loop can access it. On every state change, call notify_accesskit_surface to push the diff into the WP-011 accessibility/ surface. Do NOT poll; push-on-change only (HBR-QUIET).
